BAXTER, Respondent, v. NEW YORK STATE MUT. BEN. ASS’N, Appellant (three cases). (Supreme Court, General Term, Fourth Department. May 18, 1894.) Actions by Mary F. Baxter against the New York State Mutual Benefit Association.

Argued before HARDIN, P. J., and MARTIN and MERWIN, JJ.

No opinions. Orders reversed, with $10 costs and disbursements in each case, and motion granted in each case, with $10 costs in one case only.
